Trial 1:

Dear Women,

You are not too much, and you never were. Your voice, your emotions, your ambitions—they are not burdens to carry quietly, but strengths to be seen and heard. The world may try to shape you into something smaller, something easier to manage, but you were not made to shrink.

You are allowed to take up space. To lead, to rest, to change your mind, to start over. You are allowed to be soft and powerful at the same time. There is no single way to be you—and that is your greatest freedom.

Remember that your worth is not measured by how much you give to others at the expense of yourself. You deserve the same care, patience, and love that you so often offer.

Keep going, even on the days you doubt yourself. There is strength in your persistence, beauty in your individuality, and power in your story.

With respect and admiration,
Always.

