Trial 2:

Dear Women,

You are powerful in ways the world doesn’t always stop to recognize. In your resilience, your compassion, your quiet strength, and your loud courage—you carry more than you’re often given credit for.

You build, you nurture, you lead, you endure. You show up even when it’s hard, even when no one is watching. And that matters more than words can fully capture.

May you always remember your worth is not defined by expectations, opinions, or limitations placed on you by others. It is inherent. It is yours.

Keep rising, keep speaking, keep becoming everything you want to be—on your own terms.

With respect and admiration.

